cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new inference principle for mixup-trained models to improve their adversarial robustness. It also involves training deep networks and improving their generalization performance. Additionally, the paper uses datasets commonly used in computer vision tasks, such as CIFAR-10 and CIFAR-100, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also deals with defending against adversarial attacks, which is a common topic in the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper involves improving model robustness, which is a topic that can be related to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
